query: What are the population sizes of the cities in the Southwestern Indiana region in comparison to the cities in the Western Coal Fields and Eastern Little Egypt regions?
summary: The city populations in Southwestern Indiana area change, but usually they are bigger than in Western Coal Fields and Eastern Little Egypt areas. The biggest city in Southwestern Indiana area is Evansville, with people of 117,429 in 2010, it is over two times bigger than population of Owensboro in Western Coal Fields area, that is 57,265. Other big cities with many people in Southwestern Indiana area are Vincennes, Jasper, Washington, Princeton, Tell City, Mount Vernon, Boonville, Huntingburg, with people between 5,594 and 18,423. When comparing, the Western Coal Fields area only has five cities in top fifteen list, with people between 5,893 and 28,757. The Eastern Little Egypt area has fewer cities in top fifteen list, only three cities with people from 8,282 to 9,638.
